article.description: — Aaryn Rai had 13 points and 13 rebounds to lift Dartmouth to a 76-54 win over Harvard on Saturday.
article.headline: Rai carries Dartmouth over Harvard 76-54
article.story: BOSTON -- — Aaryn Rai had 13 points and 13 rebounds to lift Dartmouth to a 76-54 win over Harvard on Saturday. Brendan Barry had 19 points for Dartmouth (9-16, 6-8 Ivy League). Taurus Samuels added 15 points. Dame Adelekun had 12 points and eight rebounds. Noah Kirkwood had 19 points for the Crimson (13-13, 5-9). Kale Catchings added 11 points and seven rebounds. The Big Green leveled the season series against the Crimson. Harvard defeated Dartmouth 60-59 on Jan. 17. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
